Class AccessorContainer<E>

  • java.lang.Object
    • ch.nolix.core.container.AccessorContainer<E>
  • Type Parameters:
    E - - The type of the elements of an accessor container.
    All Implemented Interfaces:
    IContainer<E>, java.lang.Iterable<E>

    public final class AccessorContainer<E>
extends java.lang.Object
implements IContainer<E>
    An accessor container provides methods to access of a given container, but prevents that the given container can be muated.

    Silvan Wyss
